@jeenbroekstra this is what I am proposing now. A general way to track result sizes across all iterators in the query plan. This also makes it simpler to enable or disable. I was thinking of something along the lines of:
if(trackResultSize()){
    expr.setResultSizeActual(Math.max(0, expr.getResultSizeActual()));
    ret = new ResultSizeCountingIterator(ret, expr);
}

return ret;

How can we make this configurable for the user?

